    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/15329</id>
    <published>2012-11-09T00:00:00+00:00</published>
    <updated>2012-11-09T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/heavy-goods-vehicle-speed-limit-increase-evaluation-final-report"/>
    <title>Heavy goods vehicle speed limit increase evaluation: final report</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Department for Transport commissioned the Transport Research Laboratory (TRL) to provide an evidence-base, analysis and reasoned opinion on whether or not there is likely to be any road safety risk involved in increasing the speed limit of heavy good vehicles exceeding 7.5 tonnes on single carriageway de-restricted roads from 40mph to 50mph (or possibly 45mph). This report gives detail on the findings of the research.&lt;/p&gt;

